// Instructions:
// 1. Start with I-IV-V-I (already active)
// 2. Listen repeatedly until you can anticipate the chord changes
// 3. Try singing or humming along with the progression
// 4. Uncomment one progression at a time to learn each one
// 5. Notice how different progressions create different emotions
// 6. Advanced: Try to identify which progression you're hearing

// Tips:
// - I (C) = home/stable
// - IV (F) = movement away from home
// - V (G) = tension/wants to resolve to I
// - vi (Am) = relative minor, sounds melancholic
// - ii (Dm) = pre-dominant, leads to V
